+## 12. Update: Implemented Fixes (2025-12-01)
+
+Following the analysis in Section 11, the following fixes were implemented and built into the kernel.
+
+### 12.1 Fix 1: RTU (Ray Tracing Unit) Enablement
+
+**Files Modified**:
+- `drivers/gpu/drm/panthor/panthor_regs.h`
+- `drivers/gpu/drm/panthor/panthor_gpu.c`
+
+**Implementation**:
+
+Added `SHADER_PWRFEATURES` register definition:
+```c
+/* panthor_regs.h */
+#define SHADER_PWRFEATURES              0x188
+#define   SHADER_PWRFEATURES_RTU_EN     BIT(0)
+```
+
+Added RTU enablement in Sky1-specific GPU initialization:
+```c
+/* panthor_gpu.c - in panthor_gpu_init() Sky1 block */
+/* Enable Ray Tracing Unit subdomain for shader cores */
+gpu_write(ptdev, SHADER_PWRFEATURES, SHADER_PWRFEATURES_RTU_EN);
+```
+
+**Rationale**: G720 Immortalis has ray tracing hardware. If RTU subdomain isn't enabled but shader code expects it, jobs may hang.
+
+### 12.2 Fix 2: TITANHW_2938 L2 Power Transition Wait
+
+**File Modified**: `drivers/gpu/drm/panthor/panthor_mmu.c`
+
+**Implementation**:
+
+Added L2 power transition wait after MMU flush operations:
+```c
+/* panthor_mmu.c - in mmu_queue_command() after issuing AS_COMMAND */
+/*
+ * G720 HW issue: After MMU flush, wait for L2 power transition
+ * to complete. Without this, MMU operations can race with L2
+ * power state changes, causing GPU lockup.
+ */
+if (op == AS_COMMAND_FLUSH_MEM) {
+    u64 val;
+
+    ret = gpu_read64_relaxed_poll_timeout(ptdev, L2_PWRTRANS,
+                         val, val == 0,
+                         100, 2000000);
+    if (ret)
+        drm_warn(&ptdev->base,
+             "L2_PWRTRANS timeout: 0x%llx", val);
+}
+```
+
+**Rationale**: This implements the TITANHW_2938 workaround. After MMU flush when L2 is in transition, wait for `L2_PWRTRANS == 0`. Without this, MMU operations can race with L2 power state changes, potentially corrupting GPU state.
+
+### 12.3 Fix 3: Extended IRQ Mask Bits
+
+**Files Modified**:
+- `drivers/gpu/drm/panthor/panthor_fw.h`
+- `drivers/gpu/drm/panthor/panthor_fw.c`
+- `drivers/gpu/drm/panthor/panthor_sched.c`
+
+**Implementation**:
+
+Added GLB_FATAL bit definition and extended GLB_EVT_MASK:
+```c
+/* panthor_fw.h */
+#define GLB_FATAL               BIT(27)
+#define GLB_EVT_MASK            GENMASK(27, 20)  /* Was GENMASK(26, 20) */
+```
+
+Extended `ack_irq_mask` with additional bits:
+```c
+/* panthor_fw.c - in panthor_fw_init() */
+glb_iface->input->ack_irq_mask = GLB_CFG_ALLOC_EN |
+                 GLB_PING |
+                 GLB_CFG_PROGRESS_TIMER |
+                 GLB_CFG_POWEROFF_TIMER |
+                 GLB_PROTM_ENTER |      /* NEW */
+                 GLB_PROTM_EXIT |       /* NEW */
+                 GLB_FWCFG_UPDATE |     /* NEW */
+                 GLB_IDLE_EN |
+                 GLB_IDLE |
+                 GLB_FATAL;             /* NEW */
+```
+
+Added GLB_FATAL handling in scheduler:
+```c
+/* panthor_sched.c - in sched_process_global_irq_locked() */
+if (evts & GLB_FATAL) {
+    drm_err(&ptdev->base,
+        "GPU firmware fatal error: req=0x%08x ack=0x%08x",
+        req, ack);
+    /* Acknowledge the fatal event */
+    panthor_fw_update_reqs(glb_iface, req, ack, GLB_FATAL);
+}
+```
+
+**Rationale**: Enables firmware fatal error notifications (GLB_FATAL), protected mode transitions, and firmware config updates. This allows the driver to catch and report GPU firmware errors earlier rather than waiting for timeout.
