+## 13. Critical Update: G720 64-bit endpoint_req (2025-12-01)
+
+### 13.1 Root Cause of CSG Timeout - FOUND AND FIXED
+
+**Discovery**: G720 uses a completely different CSG endpoint_req register layout than older GPUs.
+
+| GPU Generation | Register | Offset | Size |
+|----------------|----------|--------|------|
+| Pre-G720 | `CSG_EP_REQ_LO` | 0x34 | 32-bit |
+| G720+ (arch >= 12) | `CSG_EP_REQ_LO_64B_ALIGNED` | 0x38 | 64-bit |
+
+**The Problem**: Panthor was writing endpoint configuration to offset 0x34. G720 firmware **ignores** this register entirely and expects the data at offset 0x38 in 64-bit format.
+
+**Vendor Driver Code** (`mali_kbase_csf_scheduler.c:3137-3146`):
+```c
+if (kbdev->gpu_props.gpu_id.arch_id >= GPU_ID_ARCH_MAKE(14, 8, 4)) {
+    // G720+ uses 64-bit register at different offset
+    kbase_csf_fw_io_group_write64(fw_io, slot, CSG_EP_REQ_LO_64B_ALIGNED, ep_cfg);
+} else {
+    // Older GPUs use 32-bit register
+    kbase_csf_fw_io_group_write(fw_io, slot, CSG_EP_REQ_LO, ep_cfg);
+}
+```
+
+### 13.2 Implementation Fix
+
+**Files Modified**:
+- `drivers/gpu/drm/panthor/panthor_fw.h` - Added `endpoint_req_hi` field and G720 macros
+- `drivers/gpu/drm/panthor/panthor_sched.c` - Three locations updated for G720 handling
+
+**panthor_fw.h changes**:
+```c
+u32 endpoint_req;
+/*
+ * G720+ uses 64-bit endpoint_req at offset 0x38 (endpoint_req_64).
+ * Older GPUs use 32-bit endpoint_req at 0x34 + endpoint_req_hi at 0x38.
+ */
+#define CSG_EP_REQ_NEURAL(x)           (((u64)(x) << 32) & GENMASK_ULL(39, 32))
+#define CSG_EP_REQ_COMP_PRI_THRESH(x)  (((u64)(x) << 40) & GENMASK_ULL(47, 40))
+#define CSG_EP_REQ_COMP_PRI_RATIO(x)   (((u64)(x) << 48) & GENMASK_ULL(51, 48))
+u32 endpoint_req_hi;
+u32 reserved2;
+```
+
+**panthor_sched.c changes** (three locations):
+
+1. `csg_slot_prog_locked()` - Write endpoint config:
+```c
+if (GPU_ARCH_MAJOR(ptdev->gpu_info.gpu_id) >= 12) {
+    u64 ep_cfg = CSG_EP_REQ_COMPUTE(group->max_compute_cores) |
+                 CSG_EP_REQ_FRAGMENT(group->max_fragment_cores) |
+                 CSG_EP_REQ_TILER(group->max_tiler_cores) |
+                 CSG_EP_REQ_PRIORITY(priority);
+    /* For G720, write 64-bit value at offset 0x38 (endpoint_req_hi) */
+    *((u64 *)&csg_iface->input->endpoint_req_hi) = ep_cfg;
+} else {
+    csg_iface->input->endpoint_req = ...;  // Original 32-bit path
+}
+```
+
+2. `csg_slot_sync_priority_locked()` - Read priority:
+```c
+if (GPU_ARCH_MAJOR(ptdev->gpu_info.gpu_id) >= 12)
+    ep_req = csg_iface->input->endpoint_req_hi;
+else
+    ep_req = csg_iface->input->endpoint_req;
+```
+
+3. Priority update path - Update correct field for G720
+
