+## 17. Critical Fix: Initialization Sequence (2025-12-01)
+
+### 17.1 Root Cause: Incorrect Init Order
+
+Further analysis of vendor driver's `firmware_hctl_core_pwr` mode revealed the **exact initialization sequence** required:
+
+**Vendor Driver Sequence (when host controls power)**:
+1. MCU global reinit starts
+2. Host powers shader cores via `SHADER_PWRON`
+3. Host polls `SHADER_READY` until cores are ready
+4. Host writes `GLB_ALLOC_EN_LO/HI` with the READY core mask
+5. Host toggles `GLB_CFG_ALLOC_EN` request bit
+6. Host rings doorbell to notify MCU
+7. MCU acknowledges via `GLB_ACK`
+
+**Our Previous (Broken) Sequence**:
+1. Set `core_en_mask = shader_present`
+2. Toggle `GLB_CFG_ALLOC_EN`
+3. Ring doorbell
+4. THEN power shaders via legacy path ← **TOO LATE!**
+
+### 17.2 The Problem
+
+We were telling MCU "these cores are available" **before** the cores were actually powered. The MCU received the core mask, acknowledged it, but then when jobs arrived, it tried to activate cores via HOST_POWER (which doesn't work on Sky1).
+
+Even with `poweroff_timer=0` (which disables MCU's power-off logic), the MCU's job dispatch still expects cores to be "active" via HOST_POWER before using them.
+
+### 17.3 The Fix
+
+Power shaders FIRST, then notify MCU with the mask of **actually powered** cores:
+
+```c
+static void panthor_fw_init_global_iface(struct panthor_device *ptdev)
+{
+    bool is_sky1 = of_device_is_compatible(ptdev->base.dev->of_node, "cix,sky1-mali");
+    u64 shader_ready = 0;
+
+    /* Sky1: Power shaders BEFORE telling MCU about available cores */
+    if (is_sky1 && GPU_ARCH_MAJOR(ptdev->gpu_info.gpu_id) >= 12) {
+        panthor_gpu_g720_shader_power_on(ptdev);
+        shader_ready = gpu_read64(ptdev, SHADER_READY);
+    }
+
+    /* Tell MCU which cores are ACTUALLY powered */
+    if (is_sky1 && shader_ready)
+        glb_iface->input->core_en_mask = shader_ready;  /* powered cores */
+    else
+        glb_iface->input->core_en_mask = ptdev->gpu_info.shader_present;
+
+    /* Now toggle GLB_CFG_ALLOC_EN and ring doorbell */
+    /* ... */
+}
+```
+
+### 17.4 Vendor Code Reference
+
+From `mali_kbase_pm_driver.c` lines 1493-1517:
+
+```c
+case KBASE_MCU_HCTL_SHADERS_PEND_ON:
+    if (!hctl_shader_cores_power_up_done(kbdev, shaders_ready, shaders_trans,
+                                          backend->shaders_avail))
+        break;
+
+    /* Cores now stable, notify MCU the stable mask */
+    kbase_csf_firmware_update_core_attr(kbdev, false, true, shaders_ready);
+
+    backend->pm_shaders_core_mask = shaders_ready;
+    backend->mcu_state = KBASE_MCU_HCTL_CORES_NOTIFY_PEND;
+    break;
+
+case KBASE_MCU_HCTL_CORES_NOTIFY_PEND:
+    /* Wait for the acknowledgement */
+    if (kbase_csf_firmware_core_attr_updated(kbdev))
+        backend->mcu_state = KBASE_MCU_ON_HWCNT_ENABLE;
+    break;
+```
+
+The vendor driver:
+1. Powers cores (`KBASE_MCU_HCTL_SHADERS_PEND_ON`)
+2. Waits for power-up completion (`hctl_shader_cores_power_up_done`)
+3. Notifies MCU of powered cores (`kbase_csf_firmware_update_core_attr`)
+4. Waits for MCU acknowledgement (`kbase_csf_firmware_core_attr_updated`)
+5. Proceeds to normal operation
+
+### 17.5 Expected Result
+
+With the corrected sequence, the MCU should:
+1. Receive `core_en_mask` containing cores that are ALREADY POWERED
+2. See `poweroff_timer=0`, meaning don't try to manage power
+3. When jobs arrive, dispatch directly to the powered cores
+4. Cores should show `shader_pwractive != 0` during execution
+
+### 17.6 Layer 4 Final Status
+
+```
+Layer 1: Memory barrier (dmb(osh))     → Eliminated stale read hypothesis
+Layer 2: RTU/L2/IRQ mask               → Basic GPU init improvements
+Layer 3: G720 endpoint_req offset      → FIXED CSG communication
+Layer 4: Shader power management       → IMPLEMENTATION IN PROGRESS
+         ↳ HOST_POWER interface non-functional (Sky1-specific)
+         ↳ Legacy SHADER_PWRON works
+         ↳ poweroff_timer=0 disables MCU power management
+         ↳ NEW FIX: Power cores BEFORE notifying MCU
+```
+
