+# Panthor Driver Power Management Analysis
+
+## Executive Summary
+
+This document provides an exhaustive analysis of the mainline Panthor driver's power management system, focusing on the HOST_POWER interface and all related code paths. This analysis is essential for understanding how to port Sky1 GPU support given that Sky1's HOST_POWER registers are non-functional.
+
+---
+
+## 1. Register Definitions
+
+### 1.1 HOST_POWER Interface (G720/Arch >= 12)
+
+Located in `drivers/gpu/drm/panthor/panthor_regs.h`:
+
+| Register | Offset | Description |
+|----------|--------|-------------|
+| `PWR_STATUS` | 0x820 | Power domain status |
+| `PWR_COMMAND` | 0x828 | Power domain commands |
+| `PWR_READY` | 0x830 | Domain ready status |
+| `HOST_POWER_SHADER_PRESENT` | 0xA00 | Shader cores present (64-bit) |
+| `HOST_POWER_SHADER_READY` | 0xA08 | Shader cores ready (64-bit) |
+| `HOST_POWER_SHADER_PWRON` | 0xA10 | Shader power on request (64-bit) |
+| `HOST_POWER_SHADER_PWRACTIVE` | 0xA18 | Shader cores active (64-bit) |
+| `HOST_POWER_SHADER_COHERENCY` | 0xA20 | Shader coherency mask (64-bit) |
+| `HOST_POWER_TILER_PRESENT` | 0xC00 | Tiler cores present (64-bit) |
+| `HOST_POWER_TILER_READY` | 0xC08 | Tiler cores ready (64-bit) |
+| `HOST_POWER_TILER_PWRON` | 0xC10 | Tiler power on request (64-bit) |
+
+#### PWR_STATUS Bits (0x820)
+
+```c
+#define PWR_STATUS_ALLOW_L2         BIT(0)
+#define PWR_STATUS_ALLOW_TILER      BIT(4)
+#define PWR_STATUS_ALLOW_SHADER     BIT(8)
+#define PWR_STATUS_DELEGATED_L2     BIT(16)
+#define PWR_STATUS_DELEGATED_TILER  BIT(20)
+#define PWR_STATUS_DELEGATED_SHADER BIT(24)
+```
+
+#### PWR_COMMAND Values (0x828)
+
+```c
+#define PWR_COMMAND_POWER_UP    0x10
+#define PWR_COMMAND_POWER_DOWN  0x11
+#define PWR_COMMAND_DELEGATE    0x20
+#define PWR_COMMAND_RETRACT     0x21
+
+#define PWR_COMMAND_DOMAIN_L2     (0x0 << 8)
+#define PWR_COMMAND_DOMAIN_TILER  (0x4 << 8)
+#define PWR_COMMAND_DOMAIN_SHADER (0x8 << 8)
+```
+
+### 1.2 Legacy Power Interface
+
+| Register | Offset | Description |
+|----------|--------|-------------|
+| `L2_PWRON` | 0x1A0 | L2 cache power on request |
+| `L2_READY` | 0x1C0 | L2 cache ready status |
+| `SHADER_PWRON` | 0x180 | Shader power on request (64-bit) |
+| `SHADER_READY` | 0x140 | Shader ready status (64-bit) |
+| `SHADER_PWRACTIVE` | 0x240 | Shader active status (64-bit) |
+| `TILER_PWRON` | 0x190 | Tiler power on request (64-bit) |
+| `TILER_READY` | 0x150 | Tiler ready status (64-bit) |
+
+### 1.3 Sky1-Specific Registers
+
+```c
+#define GPU_PWR_KEY         0xD00   /* Unlock key register */
+#define GPU_PWR_KEY_UNLOCK  0x2968A819
+#define GPU_PWR_OVERRIDE1   0xD08   /* Power override register */
+#define SHADER_PWRFEATURES  0x188   /* Shader power features */
+#define SHADER_PWRFEATURES_RTU_EN  BIT(1)
+```
+
+---
+
+## 2. Power Domain Architecture
+
+### 2.1 Power Domains
+
+The GPU has three main power domains managed independently:
+
+1. **L2 Cache** - Must be powered first (foundation)
+2. **Tiler** - Geometry processing
+3. **Shaders** - Compute cores (most complex to manage)
+
+### 2.2 Power State Flow
+
+```
+                    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
+                    │              GPU Power Flow             │
+                    └─────────────────────────────────────────┘
+                                        │
+                    ┌───────────────────┼───────────────────┐
+                    ▼                   ▼                   ▼
+             ┌──────────┐        ┌──────────┐        ┌──────────┐
+             │    L2    │        │  Tiler   │        │ Shaders  │
+             │  Cache   │        │          │        │          │
+             └──────────┘        └──────────┘        └──────────┘
+                    │                   │                   │
+            ┌───────┴───────┐   ┌───────┴───────┐   ┌───────┴───────┐
+            │               │   │               │   │               │
+     ┌──────▼──────┐ ┌──────▼──────┐     ┌──────▼──────┐     ┌──────▼──────┐
+     │   Legacy    │ │ HOST_POWER  │     │   Legacy    │     │ HOST_POWER  │
+     │ L2_PWRON    │ │ PWR_COMMAND │     │ SHADER_PWRON│     │ DELEGATE/   │
+     │ (all arch)  │ │ (arch >= 12)│     │ (fallback)  │     │ RETRACT     │
+     └─────────────┘ └─────────────┘     └─────────────┘     └─────────────┘
+```
+
+---
+
+## 3. Power Management Functions
+
+### 3.1 Generic Block Power On/Off
+
+**File**: `drivers/gpu/drm/panthor/panthor_gpu.c`
+
+```c
+static int panthor_gpu_block_power_on(struct panthor_device *ptdev,
+                                      const char *blk_name,
+                                      u32 pwron_reg, u32 ready_reg,
+                                      u64 mask, u32 timeout_us)
+```
+
+- Writes power-on mask to `pwron_reg`
+- Polls `ready_reg` until mask bits are set
+- Uses `readx_poll_timeout()` with configurable timeout
+- Returns 0 on success, -ETIMEDOUT on failure
+
+```c
+static int panthor_gpu_block_power_off(struct panthor_device *ptdev,
+                                       const char *blk_name,
+                                       u32 pwroff_reg, u32 ready_reg,
+                                       u64 mask, u32 timeout_us)
+```
+
+- Writes power-off mask to `pwroff_reg`
+- Polls `ready_reg` until mask bits are cleared
+- Returns 0 on success, -ETIMEDOUT on failure
+
+### 3.2 L2 Cache Power
+
+**Function**: `panthor_gpu_l2_power_on()`
+
+```c
+static int panthor_gpu_l2_power_on(struct panthor_device *ptdev)
+{
+    /* Sky1 workaround: Enable power override and RTU before L2 power */
+    if (of_device_is_compatible(ptdev->base.dev->of_node, "cix,sky1-mali")) {
+        /* Unlock power configuration */
+        gpu_write(ptdev, GPU_PWR_KEY, GPU_PWR_KEY_UNLOCK);
+        /* Enable all power overrides (24 bits) */
+        gpu_write(ptdev, GPU_PWR_OVERRIDE1, 0xFFFFFF);
+        /* Enable RTU (Ready-to-Use) feature */
+        gpu_write(ptdev, SHADER_PWRFEATURES, SHADER_PWRFEATURES_RTU_EN);
+    }
+
+    /* Apply PBHA (Page-Based Hardware Attributes) if set */
+    if (ptdev->gpu->l2_features_ext1) {
+        gpu_write(ptdev, GPU_L2_FEATURES_EXT1, ptdev->gpu->l2_features_ext1);
+    }
+
+    /* Apply SYSC_ALLOC config if present */
+    if (ptdev->gpu->sysc_alloc_config) {
+        for (i = 0; i < GPU_SYSC_ALLOC_REG_COUNT; i++) {
+            gpu_write(ptdev, GPU_SYSC_ALLOC(i),
+                      ptdev->gpu->sysc_alloc_config[i]);
+        }
+    }
+
+    /* Power on L2 via legacy register */
+    return panthor_gpu_block_power_on(ptdev, "l2",
+                                      L2_PWRON, L2_READY,
+                                      ptdev->gpu_info.l2_present, 2000);
+}
+```
+
+**Key Points**:
+- L2 uses legacy registers on all architectures
+- Sky1 requires unlocking power config before L2 power
+- PBHA/SYSC configuration applied during L2 power-on
+- L2 must be powered before any other domain
+
+### 3.3 G720 Shader Power (HOST_POWER Interface)
+
+**Function**: `panthor_gpu_g720_shader_power_on()`
+
+This is the critical function for G720/arch >= 12 shader power:
+
+```c
+static int panthor_gpu_g720_shader_power_on(struct panthor_device *ptdev)
+{
+    u64 shader_present = ptdev->gpu_info.shader_present;
+    u64 ready;
+    int ret;
+
+    /* Step 1: Check if HOST_POWER is functional */
+    u64 allow = gpu_read64(ptdev, PWR_STATUS);
+
+    if (!(allow & PWR_STATUS_ALLOW_SHADER)) {
+        /* HOST_POWER not allowing shaders - try DELEGATE */
+        gpu_write(ptdev, PWR_COMMAND,
+                  PWR_COMMAND_DELEGATE | PWR_COMMAND_DOMAIN_SHADER);
+
+        ret = readx_poll_timeout(gpu_read64, ptdev, allow,
+                                 allow & PWR_STATUS_DELEGATED_SHADER,
+                                 100, 10000);
+        if (ret) {
+            drm_warn(&ptdev->base,
+                     "HOST_POWER DELEGATE timeout, falling back to legacy\n");
+            goto legacy_fallback;
+        }
+    }
+
+    /* Step 2: Try HOST_POWER shader power-on */
+    gpu_write64(ptdev, HOST_POWER_SHADER_PWRON, shader_present);
+
+    ret = readx_poll_timeout(gpu_read64, ptdev, ready,
+                             ready == shader_present,
+                             100, 100000);
+    if (!ret) {
+        drm_dbg(&ptdev->base, "G720 shaders powered via HOST_POWER\n");
+        return 0;
+    }
+
+    drm_warn(&ptdev->base,
+             "HOST_POWER shader timeout, ready=0x%llx, trying legacy\n", ready);
+
+legacy_fallback:
+    /* Step 3: Fall back to legacy SHADER_PWRON */
+    return panthor_gpu_block_power_on(ptdev, "shader",
+                                      SHADER_PWRON, SHADER_READY,
+                                      shader_present, 100000);
+}
+```
+
+**Power Flow**:
+
+```
+┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
+│           G720 Shader Power-On Flow (Panthor)                   │
+└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
+                              │
+                              ▼
+                   ┌─────────────────────┐
+                   │ Read PWR_STATUS     │
+                   │ Check ALLOW_SHADER  │
+                   └─────────────────────┘
+                              │
+              ┌───────────────┼───────────────┐
+              │ Not Allowed   │               │ Allowed
+              ▼               │               ▼
+    ┌─────────────────┐       │     ┌─────────────────────┐
+    │ DELEGATE shader │       │     │ HOST_POWER_SHADER_  │
+    │ domain to host  │       │     │ PWRON = present     │
+    └─────────────────┘       │     └─────────────────────┘
+              │               │               │
+              ▼               │               ▼
+    ┌─────────────────┐       │     ┌─────────────────────┐
+    │ Poll for        │       │     │ Poll HOST_POWER_    │
+    │ DELEGATED_SHADER│       │     │ SHADER_READY        │
+    └─────────────────┘       │     └─────────────────────┘
+              │               │               │
+              │ Timeout       │               │ Success/Timeout
+              ├───────────────┘               │
+              ▼                               ▼
+    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
+    │              Legacy Fallback                        │
+    │   SHADER_PWRON = present, poll SHADER_READY        │
+    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
+```
+
+### 3.4 Where Shader Power Is Called
+
+Shader power-on is called from `panthor_fw_init_global_iface()` in `panthor_fw.c`:
+
+```c
+static int panthor_fw_init_global_iface(struct panthor_device *ptdev)
+{
+    struct panthor_fw_global_iface *glb_iface;
+    bool is_sky1 = of_device_is_compatible(ptdev->base.dev->of_node,
+                                           "cix,sky1-mali");
+    u64 shader_ready = 0;
+
+    /* ... get interface pointer ... */
+
+    /* For Sky1 G720: Pre-power shaders before MCU config */
+    if (is_sky1 && GPU_ARCH_MAJOR(ptdev->gpu_info.gpu_id) >= 12) {
+        int ret = panthor_gpu_g720_shader_power_on(ptdev);
+        if (ret) {
+            drm_err(&ptdev->base,
+                    "Sky1: Failed to pre-power shaders: %d\n", ret);
+            return ret;
+        }
+        shader_ready = gpu_read64(ptdev, SHADER_READY);
+        drm_info(&ptdev->base,
+                 "Sky1: Shaders pre-powered, ready=0x%llx\n", shader_ready);
+    }
+
+    /* Configure MCU global interface */
+    /* ... standard configuration ... */
+
+    /* Sky1: Set core_en_mask to powered cores */
+    if (is_sky1 && shader_ready) {
+        glb_iface->input->core_en_mask = shader_ready;
+        drm_info(&ptdev->base,
+                 "Sky1: Set core_en_mask=0x%llx\n", shader_ready);
+    }
+
+    /* Sky1: Disable MCU power management */
+    if (is_sky1) {
+        glb_iface->input->poweroff_timer = 0;
+        drm_info(&ptdev->base,
+                 "Sky1: Disabled MCU poweroff_timer\n");
+    }
+
+    /* ... ring doorbell ... */
+}
+```
+
+---
+
+## 4. CSF Global Interface Power Configuration
+
+### 4.1 Global Input Interface Structure
+
+**File**: `drivers/gpu/drm/panthor/panthor_fw.h`
+
+```c
+struct panthor_fw_global_input_iface {
+    u32 req;                    /* 0x00: Request flags */
+    u32 ack_irq_mask;          /* 0x04: IRQ mask */
+    u32 doorbell_req;          /* 0x08: Doorbell request */
+    u32 reserved1;             /* 0x0C */
+    u32 progress_timer;        /* 0x10: Progress timeout (μs) */
+    u32 poweroff_timer;        /* 0x14: Power-off timeout (μs) */
+    u64 core_en_mask;          /* 0x18: Enabled core mask */
+    u32 reserved2;             /* 0x20 */
+    u32 idle_timer;            /* 0x24: Idle timeout */
+    /* ... additional fields ... */
+};
+```
+
+### 4.2 Key Power Configuration Fields
+
+| Field | Offset | Description |
+|-------|--------|-------------|
+| `poweroff_timer` | 0x14 | MCU shader power-off timer in μs. **0 = disabled** |
+| `core_en_mask` | 0x18 | 64-bit mask of cores available to MCU |
+| `idle_timer` | 0x24 | Idle detection timeout |
+
+### 4.3 Global Request Flags
+
+```c
+#define GLB_CFG_ALLOC_EN        BIT(2)  /* Enable allocation */
+#define GLB_CFG_POWEROFF_TIMER  BIT(3)  /* Enable power-off timer */
+#define GLB_CFG_PROGRESS_TIMER  BIT(4)  /* Enable progress timer */
+```
+
+### 4.4 Standard vs Sky1 Configuration
+
+**Standard G720**:
+- `poweroff_timer` = configured value (e.g., 64000 μs)
+- `core_en_mask` = `shader_present` (all possible cores)
+- MCU manages shader power via HOST_POWER internally
+
+**Sky1 Configuration**:
+- `poweroff_timer` = 0 (disabled - host controls power)
+- `core_en_mask` = `SHADER_READY` value (actually powered cores)
+- Host pre-powers shaders before MCU boot
+- MCU uses pre-powered cores, never tries to power them
+
+---
+
+## 5. Suspend/Resume Power Flow
+
+### 5.1 Platform Reset
+
+**File**: `drivers/gpu/drm/panthor/panthor_device.c`
+
+```c
+#define SKY1_RCSU_PGCTRL_OFFSET       0x218
+#define SKY1_RCSU_QCHANNEL_CLK_GATE_EN  BIT(0)
+
+static void panthor_platform_reset(struct panthor_device *ptdev)
+{
+    /* Assert reset */
+    reset_control_assert(ptdev->rstc);
+    usleep_range(10, 20);
+
+    /* Deassert reset */
+    reset_control_deassert(ptdev->rstc);
+    usleep_range(10, 20);
+
+    /* Sky1: Enable Q-channel clock gating via RCSU */
+    if (ptdev->rcsu) {
+        u32 pgctrl = readl(ptdev->rcsu + SKY1_RCSU_PGCTRL_OFFSET);
+        writel(pgctrl | SKY1_RCSU_QCHANNEL_CLK_GATE_EN,
+               ptdev->rcsu + SKY1_RCSU_PGCTRL_OFFSET);
+    }
+}
+```
+
+### 5.2 Suspend Flow
+
+```c
+static int panthor_device_suspend(struct device *dev)
+{
+    struct panthor_device *ptdev = dev_get_drvdata(dev);
+
+    /* 1. Suspend scheduler (stop job submission) */
+    panthor_sched_suspend(ptdev);
+
+    /* 2. Suspend firmware (halt MCU) */
+    panthor_fw_suspend(ptdev);
+
+    /* 3. Power off GPU (L2, shaders go down) */
+    panthor_gpu_suspend(ptdev);
+
+    /* 4. Disable clocks */
+    clk_disable_unprepare(ptdev->clks.core);
+
+    return 0;
+}
+```
+
+### 5.3 Resume Flow
+
+```c
+static int panthor_device_resume(struct device *dev)
+{
+    struct panthor_device *ptdev = dev_get_drvdata(dev);
+    int ret;
+
+    /* 1. Enable clocks */
+    ret = clk_prepare_enable(ptdev->clks.core);
+    if (ret)
+        return ret;
+
+    /* 2. Reset platform (includes Q-channel for Sky1) */
+    panthor_platform_reset(ptdev);
+
+    /* 3. Power on GPU (L2 first, then shaders if Sky1) */
+    ret = panthor_gpu_resume(ptdev);
+    if (ret)
+        goto disable_clk;
+
+    /* 4. Resume firmware (boot MCU, init interfaces) */
+    ret = panthor_fw_resume(ptdev);
+    if (ret)
+        goto suspend_gpu;
+
+    /* 5. Resume scheduler (allow job submission) */
+    panthor_sched_resume(ptdev);
+
+    return 0;
+}
+```
+
+---
+
+## 6. Scheduler Power State Debugging
+
+**File**: `drivers/gpu/drm/panthor/panthor_sched.c`
+
+On job timeout, the scheduler dumps power state for debugging:
+
+```c
+static void panthor_sched_timedout(struct drm_sched_job *sched_job)
+{
+    /* ... */
+
+    drm_warn(&ptdev->base,
+             "  GPU: status=0x%08x fault=0x%08x "
+             "shader_ready=0x%llx shader_pwractive=0x%llx\n",
+             gpu_read(ptdev, GPU_STATUS),
+             gpu_read(ptdev, GPU_FAULT_STATUS),
+             gpu_read64(ptdev, SHADER_READY),
+             gpu_read64(ptdev, SHADER_PWRACTIVE));
+
+    /* ... */
+}
+```
+
+**Key Registers Dumped**:
+- `GPU_STATUS` - Overall GPU status
+- `GPU_FAULT_STATUS` - Fault information
+- `SHADER_READY` - Which cores are powered/ready
+- `SHADER_PWRACTIVE` - Which cores are actively executing
+
+---
+
+## 7. Sky1 Power Management Issues
+
+### 7.1 Root Cause
+
+On Sky1, the HOST_POWER interface registers return 0x0:
+- `PWR_STATUS` = 0x0 (no domains allowed)
+- `HOST_POWER_SHADER_READY` = 0x0 (never reports ready)
+- HOST_POWER DELEGATE command has no effect
+
+### 7.2 Current Workarounds in Panthor
+
+1. **Power Override**: `GPU_PWR_OVERRIDE1 = 0xFFFFFF` unlocks power control
+2. **RTU Enable**: `SHADER_PWRFEATURES_RTU_EN` enables ready-to-use mode
+3. **Legacy Fallback**: `SHADER_PWRON` register still works
+4. **MCU Config**: `poweroff_timer = 0` disables MCU power management
+5. **Core Mask**: `core_en_mask = SHADER_READY` tells MCU which cores are available
+
+### 7.3 Remaining Problem
+
+Despite these workarounds, jobs still timeout with `shader_pwractive = 0x0`:
+- Shaders show as `SHADER_READY` (powered)
+- But `SHADER_PWRACTIVE` stays 0 (no job execution)
+- MCU may still be trying to use HOST_POWER internally for job dispatch
+
+---
+
+## 8. Code Location Summary
+
+| File | Function | Purpose |
+|------|----------|---------|
+| `panthor_regs.h` | - | All register definitions |
+| `panthor_gpu.c` | `panthor_gpu_block_power_on()` | Generic power on |
+| `panthor_gpu.c` | `panthor_gpu_block_power_off()` | Generic power off |
+| `panthor_gpu.c` | `panthor_gpu_l2_power_on()` | L2 power with Sky1 workaround |
+| `panthor_gpu.c` | `panthor_gpu_g720_shader_power_on()` | G720 shader power |
+| `panthor_fw.c` | `panthor_fw_init_global_iface()` | MCU power config |
+| `panthor_fw.h` | `struct panthor_fw_global_input_iface` | MCU interface |
+| `panthor_device.c` | `panthor_platform_reset()` | Reset with Q-channel |
+| `panthor_sched.c` | `panthor_sched_timedout()` | Power state debug dump |
+
+---
+
+## 9. Comparison: Panthor vs Vendor Driver
+
+| Aspect | Panthor (Mainline) | Vendor DKMS |
+|--------|-------------------|-------------|
+| HOST_POWER | Tries first, falls back | Skips entirely |
+| Shader power | Via HOST_POWER or legacy | `kbase_pm_shader_pwr_ctrl_power()` |
+| MCU power mgmt | poweroff_timer configurable | `firmware_hctl_core_pwr` flag |
+| Core mask | Set to present or ready | Direct register control |
+| Power tracking | Read-only monitoring | Active state machine |
+
+**Key Difference**: Vendor driver has explicit `firmware_hctl_core_pwr` flag that tells MCU "host controls power, don't try to manage it yourself." Panthor relies on `poweroff_timer = 0` to achieve similar effect.
+
+---
+
+## 10. Recommendations for Sky1 Fix
+
+Based on this analysis, the remaining issue is likely that MCU still tries to activate cores via HOST_POWER for job dispatch even with `poweroff_timer = 0`. Possible solutions:
+
+1. **Check if additional firmware flags exist** that tell MCU to skip core activation
+2. **Pre-activate shaders** before MCU boot (not just power on, but activate)
+3. **Investigate SHADER_PWRACTIVE vs SHADER_READY** difference
+4. **Check if firmware version matters** - vendor uses specific CSF FW version
+
+The porting plan in `docs/sky1-panthor-porting-plan.md` addresses these with a phased approach.
+
+---
+
+## Appendix: All Power-Related Code Paths
+
+```
+panthor_device_probe()
+  └─► panthor_device_init()
+        └─► panthor_gpu_init()
+              ├─► panthor_gpu_l2_power_on()     [Sky1: PWR_OVERRIDE1, RTU]
+              └─► [continue to FW init]
+                    └─► panthor_fw_init()
+                          └─► panthor_fw_init_global_iface()
+                                ├─► panthor_gpu_g720_shader_power_on() [Sky1]
+                                ├─► Set core_en_mask = SHADER_READY
+                                └─► Set poweroff_timer = 0
+
+panthor_device_suspend()
+  ├─► panthor_sched_suspend()
+  ├─► panthor_fw_suspend()
+  └─► panthor_gpu_suspend()
+
+panthor_device_resume()
+  ├─► panthor_platform_reset()  [Sky1: Q-channel clock gate]
+  ├─► panthor_gpu_resume()
+  │     └─► panthor_gpu_l2_power_on()
+  └─► panthor_fw_resume()
+        └─► panthor_fw_init_global_iface()
+              └─► [Same Sky1 path as init]
+```
