+# Sky1 Panthor GPU Porting Plan
+
+## Executive Summary
+
+The CIX Sky1 SoC uses an Arm Immortalis-G720 GPU. While mainline Panthor driver supports G720, Sky1 has a **non-functional HOST_POWER interface** (registers return 0x0). This requires implementing host-controlled shader power mode, mirroring what the vendor driver does.
+
+### Current Status
+
+| Component | Status | Notes |
+|-----------|--------|-------|
+| Firmware boot | ✅ Working | CSF FW v3.13.0 |
+| CSG communication | ✅ Working | 64-bit endpoint_req fix applied |
+| Shader power-on | ✅ Working | Legacy SHADER_PWRON fallback |
+| EGL context | ✅ Working | test_panthor passes |
+| Job execution | ❌ Failing | `shader_pwractive=0x0` |
+
+### Root Cause
+
+MCU firmware internally uses HOST_POWER to activate cores for job execution. On Sky1:
+- HOST_POWER registers return 0x0
+- MCU can't activate cores via HOST_POWER
+- Jobs timeout waiting for core activation
+
+### Solution
+
+Implement **host-controlled power mode** in Panthor for Sky1:
+1. Host powers shaders via legacy registers BEFORE MCU boot
+2. Set `poweroff_timer = 0` to disable MCU power management
+3. Set `core_en_mask` to actual powered cores
+4. MCU dispatches jobs to pre-powered cores
+
+---
+
+## Implementation Plan
+
+### Phase 1: Shader Pre-Power (panthor_gpu.c)
+
+**Goal**: Power shaders via legacy path before MCU initialization.
+
+**File**: `drivers/gpu/drm/panthor/panthor_gpu.c`
+
+#### Step 1.1: Add Sky1 Detection Helper
+
+```c
+static bool panthor_gpu_is_sky1(struct panthor_device *ptdev)
+{
+    return of_device_is_compatible(ptdev->base.dev->of_node, "cix,sky1-mali");
+}
+```
+
+#### Step 1.2: Create Sky1 Shader Power Function
+
+```c
+static int panthor_gpu_sky1_power_shaders(struct panthor_device *ptdev)
+{
+    u64 shader_present, shader_ready;
+    int ret;
+
+    /* Read shader core mask from GPU */
+    shader_present = gpu_read64(ptdev, GPU_SHADER_PRESENT);
+    if (!shader_present) {
+        drm_err(&ptdev->base, "Sky1: No shader cores present\n");
+        return -ENODEV;
+    }
+
+    /* Power on all shaders via legacy register */
+    gpu_write64(ptdev, SHADER_PWRON, shader_present);
+
+    /* Wait for cores to power up (poll SHADER_READY) */
+    ret = readx_poll_timeout(gpu_read64, ptdev, shader_ready,
+                             shader_ready == shader_present,
+                             100, 100000);
+    if (ret) {
+        drm_err(&ptdev->base, "Sky1: Shader power-on timeout, ready=0x%llx expected=0x%llx\n",
+                shader_ready, shader_present);
+        return ret;
+    }
+
+    drm_info(&ptdev->base, "Sky1: Shaders powered via legacy path, ready=0x%llx\n",
+             shader_ready);
+
+    /* Store for later use by firmware init */
+    ptdev->gpu->sky1_shader_ready = shader_ready;
+
+    return 0;
+}
+```
+
+#### Step 1.3: Call from GPU Init
+
+In `panthor_gpu_init()`, after L2 is powered but before firmware:
+
+```c
+int panthor_gpu_init(struct panthor_device *ptdev)
+{
